  "original_title": "Sri Lanka to change laws to facilitate State Timber Corporation exports",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka to change laws to facilitate State Timber Corporation exports",
      "author": "Chanka Jayasinghe",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECOOMYNEXT \u2013\u00a0 Sri Lanka\u2019s cabinet of ministers have approved a proposed amendment to a law that will enable the State Timber Corporation to to export timber and collaborate with the private, an official said.",
        "Cabinet spokesman Bandula Gunawardena told reporters at the weekly cabinet press briefing on Tuesday August 23 that approval has been granted to amend the State Industrial Corporations Act (No 49 of 1957) which the State Timber Corporation was established under, in accordance with the current objectives of the government and the country.",
        "\u201cLately the timber corporation has been mostly engaged in value addition activities. Many furniture and other products are presented by designers in the corporation and these products have a great value in the international market as well,\u201d said Gunawardena.",
        "However, he said, the corporation does not have the authority to export its products, and amendments will be made to the relevant act to give the corporation permission to export and collaborate with the private sector in a bid to improve businesses, he said.\u00a0 (Colombo/Aug23/2022)"
      ],
